git vstatus [<options>] [--] [<ref>...] - Display version status.

    -h|--help               display help
    -q|--quiet              low verbosity
    --alpha                 assume next version is in alpha pre-release
    --beta                  assume next version is in beta pre-release
    --rc                    assume next version is in rc pre-release
    --rtm                   assume next version is in rtm (remove pre-release)
    -r|--recursive          traverse modules recursively
    <git-for options>       git for options when --recursive is specified
    <ref>...                ref to display status on (default to HEAD)
    
example:
    git vstatus -r
    git vstatus master
